Here's a summary of the A2A .NET SDK:

Key Details:
- Version: v0.2.1
- Implements Google's Agent2Agent (A2A) Protocol
- Supports .NET 9.0, .NET 8.0, and .NET Standard 2.0
- Designed for ASP.NET Core applications

Main Features:
- JSON-RPC communication
- Task management and execution
- Real-time streaming responses
- OpenTelemetry integration
- Multi-agent communication support

Core Components:
1. A2A Core Library
2. A2A.AspNetCore Integration
3. Sample Projects

Code Example (Echo Agent):
```csharp
public class EchoAgent
{
    public Task<Message> ProcessMessage(MessageSendParams messageSendParams)
    {
        var messageText = messageSendParams.Message.Parts.OfType<TextPart>().First().Text;
        var message = new Message()
        {
            Role = MessageRole.Agent,
            Parts = [new TextPart() { Text = $"Echo: {messageText}" }]
        };
        return Task.FromResult(message);
    }
}
```

Integration Example:
```csharp
app.MapA2A(taskManager, "/echo");
app.MapHttpA2A(taskManager, "/echo");
```

Use Cases:
- AI Agent Systems
- Microservice Communication
- Workflow Engines
- Multi-agent Chatbots

The SDK provides a flexible framework for building intelligent agent communication systems in .NET.

